column5: I have been a member of OFC for a while now and havent posted too many reports of my own. This year i have been fishing a lot more and have recently dusted off my camera and began to take pictures of my catch. Last week we did some night fishing for walleye, and also got out for some largemouth bass. The first picture is of my walleye 27 inches 8.4 lbs on the scale.
largemouth bass didnt get a weight or measurement anyone have any ideas?
and my buddy with a decent largie p.s i dont know how to make the pictures go all in one post sorry about that.  Thanks for viewing bassmaster4
try photobucket... then copy IMG, paste it here.. by the way nice waleye!
